                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1781">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/56.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your instructions August 13 complied with. Panaman Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    agreed this morning that the United States <pb facs="1163" n="1047"
                        xml:id="pg_1047"/> should take complete control of wireless telegraph
                    situation in both the Republic of Panama and its territorial waters. I at once
                    notified Governor Goethals and he notified Lieut. Crenshaw, who has taken charge
                    of the situation.</p>
                <p>Panaman President then issued a decree carrying out said agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
